    dc:creator "Bollino, Maurizio; Uliana, Marco; Sabatinelli, Guido" ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "The Pygopleurus Motschulsky (Coleoptera: Scarabaeoidea: Glaphyridae) of mainland Greece: taxonomy, faunistics and ecological notes" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458874>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458907>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458911>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458856>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458864> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458874>
    dc:description "FIGURES 56–67. Variability of paramera of Pygopleurus chrysonotus (Brullé, 1832) (56–61) and P. scutellatus (Brullé, 1832) (62–67). Left paramere in lateral and dorsal view. 56, Achaia; 57, Attika, Vravrona; 58, Central Macedonia, Koustochori; 59, Elis, Foloi; 60, Epirus, Mt. Tymfi; 61, Macedonia, Valandovo; 62, Argolis, Achladokampos; 63, Elis, Figalia; 64, Korinthia, Galatas; 65, Lakonia, Paleopanagia; 66, Messinia, Kazarma; 67, Messinia, Messini." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3458874/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458907>
    dc:description "FIGURES 128–130. Habitus of type specimens. 128, Pygopleurus chrysonotus (Brullé, 1832), neotype; 129, Pygopleurus bulgaricus (Nedelkov, 1905), neotype; 130, Pygopleurus viridisuturatus (Reitter, 1903), holotype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3458907/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458911>
    dc:description "FIGURES 131–136. Variability in the shape of elytra. Apex of right elytron. 131, Pygopleurus apicalis (Brullé, 1832), male; 132, Pygopleurus apicalis, female; 133, Pygopleurus hirsutus (Brullé, 1832), male; 134, Pygopleurus hirsutus, female; 135, Pygopleurus viridisuturatus (Reitter, 1903), female; 136, Pygopleurus chrysonotus (Brullé, 1832), male." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3458911/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458856>
    dc:description "FIGURES 33–39. Pygopleurus chrysonotus (Brullé, 1832), habitus (see also Figs. 40–42, 128) and genitalia (see also Figs. 43, 56–61). 33, male, common copper form (Euboea, Ritsona); 34, male, common copper form with unusually bright orange abdominal hair (Achaia, Kernitsa); 35, female, common red form (Beotia, Lüka Plateau); 36, female, with unusual black and white checkered abdominal hair (Euboea, Ritsona); 37, left paramere in lateral and dorsal view (Beotia, Mt. Parnassus); 38, everted endophallus in left lateral view (Beotia, Mt. Parnassus); 39, left genital sclerites of female (Thessaly, Panagia)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3458856/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458864>
    dc:description "FIGURE 44. Pygopleurus chrysonotus (Brullé, 1832): geographical, altitudinal, and temporal distribution of records. Red curves showing the expected distribution if the species was uniformly present at all heights and all times (see Material and methods)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3458864/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

